  "Enrico Preziosi is the founder and owner of Giochi Preziosi, Italy's largest toymaker.",
  "He founded Giochi Preziosi in 1978 and the company licenses toys for brands including Disney, Fortnite and Pokemon.",
  "In January 2020, he sold a 4% stake in the company to a group of investors including a Vatican-linked investment fund.",
  "Preziosi is also the owner and president of Italian soccer club Genoa CFC; in the past, he's owned several other lower-league teams."
